<font color="#FF0000">INVALIDATION</font><br>
<tt>Fri Jan 31 15:37:17 US/Eastern 1997
</tt><p>
To Nurse Ratchet,<br><br>
&gt;How come e-v-e-r-y time someone posts on these many, many pages that they did not serve in Vietnam that are immediately ripped by Vietnam Vets?<br><br>
Gee, Nurse Ratchet, I AM A VIETNAM VET, and yet I was the first one to extend myself to you and ask imput from you as to your views.  I did not care what they were, but just wanted to hear you participate in a meaningful dialog.  So what, I don't count?  You were just waiting for the likes of Spatz disguised as a vet to rip you apart so you could respond?  I understood what you meant by that one-liner, and agree with it, but many folks here put their butts on the line by being just a little more detailed about their feelings, views, and background.  I had been the first one who had stated that I accept whatever you had to contribute without a need to identify yourself.  I had never, never, never said that I or other vets were the only ones who were qualified to speak about the war, both in Nam or here at home.  Just the opposite, I put my ass on the line to explain the best that I could, that I AM NOT qualified to discuss what was occuring in those days.  Before you even said so, I DID ADMIT to having tunnel vision and said so using those exact words.  So, before lumping vets in one rotten apple basket, look around you for those who have been trying to give you encouragement and support what ever your views.  Alot of us have the anger and bitterness that you speak of, vets and non-vets.  I had believed that there was something in you that I could learn from.  It just pisses me off to no end and hurts like hell that you chose to ignore what I tried to give you.  That what I had to contribute TO YOU was invalid.  I'll be damn if I ever put myself out in public like that again, on this site or any other!<br><br>

<p><code>-- docdel@maui.net  (Doc Del) </code><p>


